-- Airbus, Airlines Ask Europe Leaders for Emissions-Cap Compromise
-- B y   N e i l   D e n s l o w
-- 2012-03-12T07:23:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-12/airbus-airlines-ask-europe-leaders-for-emissions-cap-compromise.html
The chief executive officers of
Airbus SAS,  Air Berlin Plc (AB1)  and British Airways were among
industry CEOs to sign letters asking European leaders to seek a
comprise on aviation-emissions levies amid concerns of a trade
war, according to a statement from Airbus.  The other signatories included the heads of the Air France,
Iberia,  Deutsche Lufthansa AG (LHA) ,  MTU Aero Engines Holding AG (MTX) ,
 Safran SA (SAF)  and Virgin Atlantic, the planemaker said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Neil Denslow at 
 ndenslow@bloomberg.net  